13/07/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Troops with the 1st US Armored Division are heading to Bulgaria and Romania for a month of training aimed at increasing co-operation, the US newspaper Stars and Stripes reported on Tuesday (12 July). 
The manoeuvres begin in Bulgaria with a five-day exercise testing the ability to deploy quickly. 
The larger drill, in Romania, would include 1,300 US troops and 300 Romanian soldiers. 
(Stars and Stripes, BTA, Mediapool - 12/07/05)
